question: Please list the names of all the car models whose origin country is the USA.
llm_answer: SELECT T1.car_name FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T2.country = T3.origin WHERE T3.country = 'USA' COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT DISTINCT T1.car_name FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T2.country = T3.origin WHERE T3.country = 'USA'

question: Among the cars with an acceleration of over 10 miles per squared hour, how many of them cost more than $20000 and less than $30000?
llm_answer: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN price AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.acceleration > 10 AND T2.price > 20000 AND T2.price < 30000 COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN price AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.acceleration > 10 AND T2.price BETWEEN 20000 AND 30000

question: What is the maximum sweep volume of a car that costs less than $30000?
llm_answer: SELECT MAX(T1.displacement) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN price AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.price < 30000 COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT MAX(T1.displacement / T1.cylinders) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN price AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.price < 30000

question: What is the miles per square hour of the cheapest car produced by the USA?
llm_answer: SELECT T4.mpg FROM price AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T3.origin = T2.country INNER JOIN data AS T4 ON T4.ID = T1.ID WHERE T3.country = 'USA' ORDER BY T1.price ASC LIMIT 1 COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT T4.acceleration FROM price AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T3.origin = T2.country INNER JOIN data AS T4 ON T4.ID = T1.ID WHERE T3.country = 'USA' ORDER BY T1.price ASC LIMIT 1

question: Which country produced the highest number of cars? Calculate the annual average number of cars that the said country produced from the very start to the present.
llm_answer: COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT T2.country, CAST(COUNT(T1.ID) AS REAL) / COUNT(DISTINCT T1.model_year) FROM production AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.country = T2.origin GROUP BY T2.country ORDER BY COUNT(T2.country) DESC LIMIT 1

question: What is the percentage of cars that was produced by Japan among those that have a sweep volume of no less than 30?
llm_answer: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T3.country = 'Japan' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T2.country = T3.origin WHERE T1.displacement >= 30 COLLATE NOCASE
correct_answer: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T3.country = 'Japan' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T3.origin = T2.country WHERE T1.displacement / T1.cylinders > 30

correct_answer: SELECT T4.ID FROM price AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T3.origin = T2.country INNER JOIN data AS T4 ON T4.ID = T1.ID WHERE T3.country = 'Japan' AND T1.price > 3500 AND T4.acceleration = 14

question: Calculate the difference between the number of cars that has a horsepower of 130 with the model year 1970 and model year 1976
